[33mcommit 70bc5425d59006411b8e5e997fe564007f830692[m[33m ([m[1;31morigin/claude/fix-backend-connection-014yeKjhyrdqAuN18rsJpaSC[m[33m)[m
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Nov 22 19:50:57 2025 +0000

    Move quiz settings to sidebar instead of separate dialog
    
    Changed quiz settings display from a separate dialog to an integrated
    sidebar panel for better user experience.
    
    Changes:
    - Added quizSettingsPanel to QuizPanel.cs: New panel in sidebar for settings
      * Displays quiz information (title, choices, mode)
      * Shows editable settings: Start with slide, Minimize window, Auto-close
      * Includes "Back" button to return to quiz creation panel
      * Includes "Run Quiz" button to insert quiz button to slide
    
    - Added InitializeQuizSettingsPanel(): Creates all UI controls for settings
      * Quiz info display area with gray background
      * Checkboxes for start with slide and minimize window
      * Auto-close time dropdown (1, 2, 3, 5, 10 minutes)
      * Proper spacing and consistent styling with rest of add-in
    
    - Added ShowQuizSettings() public method: Called from QuizListForm
      * Accepts quiz details, answers, and correct index
      * Updates UI labels with quiz information
      * Sets default values from quiz settings
      * Switches visibility to show settings panel
    
    - Added event handlers:
      * BtnCancelSettings_Click(): Returns to quiz panel
      * BtnRunSelectedQuiz_Click(): Inserts quiz button with settings
      * SetAutoCloseComboBox(): Helper to set dropdown from minutes value
    
    - Updated QuizListForm.cs: Call sidebar instead of dialog
      * When "Run Quiz" clicked, calls ShowQuizSettings() on QuizPanel
      * Closes quiz list form so sidebar is visible
      * No longer uses QuizSettingsForm dialog
    
    - Removed QuizSettingsForm.cs: No longer needed
    - Updated ClassPointQuiz.csproj: Removed QuizSettingsForm reference
    
    Benefits:
    - Settings stay in sidebar - no popup dialogs blocking view
    - Consistent UI experience throughout add-in
    - Easy navigation between quiz list and settings
    - Settings visible while working on slides
    - Cleaner, more integrated user interface

[33mcommit 9b46500cb004e7f2e5f3bcfb9fe8641187151160[m
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Nov 22 19:44:49 2025 +0000

    Add quiz settings dialog when selecting quiz to run
    
    Added a new QuizSettingsForm that displays when selecting an existing quiz to run,
    allowing users to review and edit quiz settings before running the quiz.
    
    Changes:
    - Created QuizSettingsForm.cs: New dialog showing quiz information and editable settings
      * Displays quiz title, number of choices, allow multiple, and quiz mode
      * Allows editing: Start with slide, Minimize window, Auto-close time
      * User can choose to run quiz or cancel
    
    - Updated QuizListForm.cs: Show settings dialog before running quiz
      * When "Run Quiz" button is clicked, show QuizSettingsForm first
      * Only proceed to insert quiz button if user confirms in dialog
      * Display selected settings in success message
      * Handle cancel action by re-enabling the button
    
    - Updated ThisAddIn.cs: Added static properties for new settings
      * Added StartWithSlide property (default: false)
      * Added MinimizeWindow property (default: false)
      * These settings can be used when quiz is started during presentation
    
    - Updated ClassPointQuiz.csproj: Added QuizSettingsForm to compilation
    
    Benefits:
    - Users can now review quiz details before running
    - Settings can be adjusted per session without recreating quiz
    - Better user experience with clear visibility of quiz configuration
    - Consistent settings management across create and run flows

