    Fix auto-close timer bug - incorrect minutes calculation
    
    Fixed two bugs with auto-close timer:
    
    1. Parse actual minutes from ComboBox text instead of using index
       - Previous: SelectedIndex + 1 (caused 5minâ†’4, 10minâ†’5)
       - ComboBox items: "1 minute", "2 minutes", "3 minutes", "5 minutes", "10 minutes"
       - Now: Parse integer from selected text (e.g., "5 minutes" â†’ 5)
       - This ensures correct values: 1, 2, 3, 5, 10 minutes
    
    2. Use updated value from QuizConfigForm after dialog closes
       - Previous: Used initial autoCloseMinutes from QuizPanel
       - Now: Uses configForm.AutoCloseMinutes (respects user changes in dialog)
    
    The timer will now correctly apply the selected duration.

